Keyframe creates some odd inconsistencies if it's active on all CNets, so if you use multiple CNets maybe disconnect keyframe from some of them.

nodes.title: Save separate PNG from batch - location

widgets_values:
Controls resolution, batch, and upscale factor for Highres.
Switches for Source and Cnet. 

Source external - single image multiplied by batch or video.

Source to Cnet - single image or video.

If you use Source external with an image, play with the denoise. Also try using keyframe with either Cnet Depth, or Cnet edge. 

-----------------------------------------------------------
AlignYourSteps-samplers behave differently with motion scale, so try adjusting it especially if you do txt2vid with no IPadater or Cnets. AYS also needs one of the dpmpp samplers.
-----------------------------------------------------------



GET motion model v3 and the motion adapter v3
Controlnet models and the ip adapter models.


Reselect all models, loras, vae etc. to make sure they are correctly selected as i have some of them in custom locations.

Controlpanels to turn on or off things.


Generate low res preview by having everything off in the "Main" (unless you are using motion lora) till you get something you like, after that turn on "Highres", "Detailer" and "Save" to generate highres version using the same seed.

FILM VFI interpolates frames so the frame rate in "Save" video combine is doubled.

If FILM VFI doesn't work for you delete it and put frame_rate back to 12 in the "Save" video combine.
Unconnected pipe with no Cnet. Incase needed for detailer, switch "Pipe All" connection to reroute with this.

Save location control. Turn them on if you want to use them, if not, delete them and turn "filename_prefix" back to widget in the "Save" video combine.

Will save mp4 + PNG and a separate PNG from batch (also saves png from preview render)

IMPORTANT!!
Change the lines in "Save separate PNG from batch - location" to match your comfyui location 
----  YOUR_COMFYUI_LOCATION\output\Animatediff_1\MP4  -----
----  YOUR_COMFYUI_LOCATION\output\Animatediff_2\MP4  -----
